This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) as it proposes a Medium Access Control (MAC) protocol for a wireless channel. It may also belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category as it deals with the transmission and reception of multiple packets. Additionally, it may belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category as wireless channels are often used for multimedia transmission. The paper also involves system-level design and analysis, which may place it in the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, it may belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category as MAC protocols are often used for security purposes.
